<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.115Am319/213</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-19T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3341. American Transatlantic Company informs Department that
                                blacklisting company’s vessels renders it difficult for company
                                obtain cargoes. The Department regrets the employment by the British
                                Government of methods of this kind which result in such great injury
                                to owners of vessels of neutral country. Continuance these vessels
                                on black list appears to have result of depriving owners of benefits
                                which were expected would follow promise British Government not to
                                seize vessels.</p>
                            <p>Communicate above to British Government and request removal vessels
                                from black list.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>